Since the data is having lots of small numbers so we are clipping the outliers so here we are replaing extreme positive outliers with 95 percetile value in the respective column and negative outliers with 5 percentile value¶

In [275]:
# ouliers treatment 
def outlier(val):
    if val> mn+3*std :
        val = np95
    elif val< mn-3*std:
         val= np05
    else :
         val= val
    return val
In [276]:
for column in df2:
    #print(column)
    mn= df2[column].mean()
    std=df2[column].std()
    np95=df2[column].quantile(0.95)
    np05=df2[column].quantile(0.05)
    df2[column]=df2[column].apply(outlier)
